      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <!--
Encoded for Siddham by Eszter Somogyi, following Ramesh and Tewari's edition unless otherwise noted in comments. Version of January 2019. Comments below by Dániel Balogh are offered "as is" and do not represent a thoroughly researched or considered opinion.
-->
        <p><lb n="1"/>valkhāḥ paramabhaṭṭāraka-pādānuddhyāto mahārāja-bhuluṇḍaḥ samājñāpayati
<lb n="2"/>sarvvān evāsmat-santakān āyuktakā<choice>
            <sic>d</sic>
            <corr>n</corr>
          </choice>
</p>
        <p>vijñātam astu vaḥ samanujānīmo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>sya
<lb n="3"/>bhāradvāja-sagotra-kusāraka-brāhmaṇasya <unclear>āṣ</unclear>āḍhaṇandi-vijñāpyā Ulla<!--
L3 RT prints aṁṣāḍhaṇandi and in a note (by their editor?) says, "better read āṣāḍhaṇandi". I think the suggestion is for an improved reading, not for an emendation; it seems possible from the rubbing and makes better sense. Also, I (DB) think kusāraka should probably be emended to kumāraka.
--><lb break="no" n="4"/>
dana-sīmāyāṁ khuddataka-pratyaya-kṣetra-paṭṭī saha-maṇḍala-kacchena brahmadeya<lb break="no" n="5"/>
m a-bhāgam ācandrā<sic>rk</sic>a-tārakā-kālīna<surplus>ṁ</surplus>m anvaya-bhojyam bhogāyaivam idānī<lb break="no" n="6"/>
m asyāsmābhiḥ kr̥tānujñasyocitayā brahmadeya-bhuktyā bhuñjata<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> kr̥ṣa<lb break="no" n="7"/>
taś ca sarvvair evāsmat-pakṣīyai<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> samanumantavyaṁ</p>
        <p><lb n="8"/>pratihāra-skando dūtakaḥ</p>
        <p>varṣe <num value="109">
            <unclear><g type="numeral">100</g> 9</unclear>
          </num> phalgu ba <num value="12"><g type="numeral">10</g> 2</num><!--
L8 RT read the date as 57, but it is very probably 109; 59 is still a more likely alternative than 57. See Balogh_Kiss_2019
--></p>
        <ab><lb n="01"/>m<choice>
            <sic>ā</sic>
            <corr>a</corr>
          </choice>hārāja-bhuluṇḍasya<!--
